    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> coated chicken </strong>and cook for 3 min on each side or until lightly browned</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve <strong>half </strong>your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>in 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
